snippet: The number of Americans covered through exchanges is expected to only inch up by the end of 2016 to 10 million, a much smaller number than earlier projections.
abstract: Obama administration predicts enrollment in public insurance marketplaces established by Affordable Care Act will not increase significantly by end of 2016; rise of 100,000 enrollees is expected, bringing total to 10 million people who have marketplace coverage.
lead_paragraph: The number of Americans covered through exchanges is expected to only inch up by the end of 2016 to 10 million, a much smaller number than earlier projections.
